     464            8 : /** @internal */
     465            8 : export const enum NodeFactoryFlags {
     466            8 :     None = 0,
     467            8 :     // Disables the parenthesizer rules for the factory.
     468            8 :     NoParenthesizerRules = 1 << 0,
     469            8 :     // Disables the node converters for the factory.
     470            8 :     NoNodeConverters = 1 << 1,
     471            8 :     // Ensures new `PropertyAccessExpression` nodes are created with the `NoIndentation` emit flag set.
     472            8 :     NoIndentationOnFreshPropertyAccess = 1 << 2,
     473            8 :     // Do not set an `original` pointer when updating a node.
     474            8 :     NoOriginalNode = 1 << 3,
     475            8 : }
     476            8 : 
     477            8 : const nodeFactoryPatchers: ((factory: NodeFactory) => void)[] = [];
     478            8 : 
     479            8 : /** @internal */
     480            8 : export function addNodeFactoryPatcher(fn: (factory: NodeFactory) => void) {
     481            8 :     nodeFactoryPatchers.push(fn);
     482            8 : }
     483            8 : 
     484            8 : /**
     485            8 :  * Creates a `NodeFactory` that can be used to create and update a syntax tree.
     486            8 :  * @param flags Flags that control factory behavior.
     487            8 :  * @param baseFactory A `BaseNodeFactory` used to create the base `Node` objects.
     488            8 :  *
     489            8 :  * @internal
     490            8 :  */
     491            8 : export function createNodeFactory(flags: NodeFactoryFlags, baseFactory: BaseNodeFactory): NodeFactory {
     492            8 :     const setOriginal = flags & NodeFactoryFlags.NoOriginalNode ? identity : setOriginalNode;
     493            8 : 
     494            8 :     // Lazily load the parenthesizer, node converters, and some factory methods until they are used.
     495            8 :     const parenthesizerRules = memoize(() => flags & NodeFactoryFlags.NoParenthesizerRules ? nullParenthesizerRules : createParenthesizerRules(factory));
     496            8 :     const converters = memoize(() => flags & NodeFactoryFlags.NoNodeConverters ? nullNodeConverters : createNodeConverters(factory));
     497            8 : 
     498            8 :     // lazy initializaton of common operator factories
     499            8 :     const getBinaryCreateFunction = memoizeOne((operator: BinaryOperator) => (left: Expression, right: Expression) => createBinaryExpression(left, operator, right));
     500            8 :     const getPrefixUnaryCreateFunction = memoizeOne((operator: PrefixUnaryOperator) => (operand: Expression) => createPrefixUnaryExpression(operator, operand));
     501            8 :     const getPostfixUnaryCreateFunction = memoizeOne((operator: PostfixUnaryOperator) => (operand: Expression) => createPostfixUnaryExpression(operand, operator));
     502            8 :     const getJSDocPrimaryTypeCreateFunction = memoizeOne(<T extends JSDocType>(kind: T["kind"]) => () => createJSDocPrimaryTypeWorker(kind));
     503            8 :     const getJSDocUnaryTypeCreateFunction = memoizeOne(<T extends JSDocType & { readonly type: TypeNode | undefined; }>(kind: T["kind"]) => (type: T["type"]) => createJSDocUnaryTypeWorker<T>(kind, type));
     504            8 :     const getJSDocUnaryTypeUpdateFunction = memoizeOne(<T extends JSDocType & { readonly type: TypeNode | undefined; }>(kind: T["kind"]) => (node: T, type: T["type"]) => updateJSDocUnaryTypeWorker<T>(kind, node, type));
     505            8 :     const getJSDocPrePostfixUnaryTypeCreateFunction = memoizeOne(<T extends JSDocType & { readonly type: TypeNode | undefined; readonly postfix: boolean; }>(kind: T["kind"]) => (type: T["type"], postfix?: boolean) => createJSDocPrePostfixUnaryTypeWorker<T>(kind, type, postfix));
     506            8 :     const getJSDocPrePostfixUnaryTypeUpdateFunction = memoizeOne(<T extends JSDocType & { readonly type: TypeNode | undefined; readonly postfix: boolean; }>(kind: T["kind"]) => (node: T, type: T["type"]) => updateJSDocPrePostfixUnaryTypeWorker<T>(kind, node, type));
     507            8 :     const getJSDocSimpleTagCreateFunction = memoizeOne(<T extends JSDocTag>(kind: T["kind"]) => (tagName: Identifier | undefined, comment?: NodeArray<JSDocComment>) => createJSDocSimpleTagWorker(kind, tagName, comment));
     508            8 :     const getJSDocSimpleTagUpdateFunction = memoizeOne(<T extends JSDocTag>(kind: T["kind"]) => (node: T, tagName: Identifier | undefined, comment?: NodeArray<JSDocComment>) => updateJSDocSimpleTagWorker(kind, node, tagName, comment));
     509            8 :     const getJSDocTypeLikeTagCreateFunction = memoizeOne(<T extends JSDocTag & { typeExpression?: JSDocTypeExpression; }>(kind: T["kind"]) => (tagName: Identifier | undefined, typeExpression?: JSDocTypeExpression, comment?: NodeArray<JSDocComment>) => createJSDocTypeLikeTagWorker(kind, tagName, typeExpression, comment));
     510            8 :     const getJSDocTypeLikeTagUpdateFunction = memoizeOne(<T extends JSDocTag & { typeExpression?: JSDocTypeExpression; }>(kind: T["kind"]) => (node: T, tagName: Identifier | undefined, typeExpression?: JSDocTypeExpression, comment?: NodeArray<JSDocComment>) => updateJSDocTypeLikeTagWorker(kind, node, tagName, typeExpression, comment));
     511            8 : 
     512            8 :     const factory: NodeFactory = {
     513            8 :         get parenthesizer() {
     514            8 :             return parenthesizerRules();
     515            8 :         },
     516            8 :         get converters() {
     517            8 :             return converters();
     518            8 :         },

    1166            8 :     // @api
    1167            8 :     function createNodeArray<T extends Node>(elements?: readonly T[], hasTrailingComma?: boolean): NodeArray<T> {
    1168            8 :         if (elements === undefined || elements === emptyArray) {
    1169            8 :             elements = [];
    1170            8 :         }
    1171            8 :         else if (isNodeArray(elements)) {
    1172            8 :             if (hasTrailingComma === undefined || elements.hasTrailingComma === hasTrailingComma) {
    1173            8 :                 // Ensure the transform flags have been aggregated for this NodeArray
    1174            8 :                 if (elements.transformFlags === undefined) {
    1175            8 :                     aggregateChildrenFlags(elements as MutableNodeArray<T>);
    1176            8 :                 }
    1177            8 :                 Debug.attachNodeArrayDebugInfo(elements);
    1178            8 :                 return elements;
    1179            8 :             }
    1180            8 : 
    1181            8 :             // This *was* a `NodeArray`, but the `hasTrailingComma` option differs. Recreate the
    1182            8 :             // array with the same elements, text range, and transform flags but with the updated
    1183            8 :             // value for `hasTrailingComma`
    1184            8 :             const array = elements.slice() as MutableNodeArray<T>;
    1185            8 :             array.pos = elements.pos;
    1186            8 :             array.end = elements.end;
    1187            8 :             array.hasTrailingComma = hasTrailingComma;
    1188            8 :             array.transformFlags = elements.transformFlags;
    1189            8 :             Debug.attachNodeArrayDebugInfo(array);
    1190            8 :             return array;
    1191            8 :         }
    1192            8 : 
    1193            8 :         // Since the element list of a node array is typically created by starting with an empty array and
    1194            8 :         // repeatedly calling push(), the list may not have the optimal memory layout. We invoke slice() for
    1195            8 :         // small arrays (1 to 4 elements) to give the VM a chance to allocate an optimal representation.
    1196            8 :         const length = elements.length;
    1197            8 :         const array = (length >= 1 && length <= 4 ? elements.slice() : elements) as MutableNodeArray<T>;
    1198            8 :         array.pos = -1;
    1199            8 :         array.end = -1;
    1200            8 :         array.hasTrailingComma = !!hasTrailingComma;
    1201            8 :         array.transformFlags = TransformFlags.None;
    1202            8 :         aggregateChildrenFlags(array);
    1203            8 :         Debug.attachNodeArrayDebugInfo(array);
    1204            8 :         return array;
    1205            8 :     }
    1206            8 : 
    1207            8 :     function createBaseNode<T extends Node>(kind: T["kind"]) {
    1208            8 :         return baseFactory.createBaseNode(kind) as Mutable<T>;
    1209            8 :     }

    1212            8 :         const node = createBaseNode(kind);

    1214            8 :         node.localSymbol = undefined; // initialized by binder
    1215            8 :         return node;
    1216            8 :     }

    1220            8 :             // copy children used for quick info
    1221            8 :             updated.typeArguments = original.typeArguments;
    1222            8 :         }
    1223            8 :         return update(updated, original);
    1224            8 :     }

    1325            8 :         if (originalKeywordKind === undefined && text) {

    1333            8 :         if (hasExtendedUnicodeEscape) node.flags |= NodeFlags.IdentifierHasExtendedUnicodeEscape;
    1334            8 :

    1336            8 :         if (node.escapedText === "await") {
    1337            8 :             node.transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsPossibleTopLevelAwait;
    1338            8 :         }
    1339            8 :         if (node.flags & NodeFlags.IdentifierHasExtendedUnicodeEscape) {
    1340            8 :             node.transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsES2015;
    1341            8 :         }
    1342            8 : 
    1343            8 :         return node;
    1344            8 :     }

    1450            8 :     function createToken<TKind extends SyntaxKind>(token: TKind): Token<TKind>;
    1451            8 :     function createToken<TKind extends SyntaxKind>(token: TKind) {
    1452            8 :         Debug.assert(token >= SyntaxKind.FirstToken && token <= SyntaxKind.LastToken, "Invalid token");
    1453            8 :         Debug.assert(token <= SyntaxKind.FirstTemplateToken || token >= SyntaxKind.LastTemplateToken, "Invalid token. Use 'createTemplateLiteralLikeNode' to create template literals.");
    1454            8 :         Debug.assert(token <= SyntaxKind.FirstLiteralToken || token >= SyntaxKind.LastLiteralToken, "Invalid token. Use 'createLiteralLikeNode' to create literals.");
    1455            8 :         Debug.assert(token !== SyntaxKind.Identifier, "Invalid token. Use 'createIdentifier' to create identifiers");
    1456            8 :         const node = createBaseToken<Token<TKind>>(token);
    1457            8 :         let transformFlags = TransformFlags.None;
    1458            8 :         switch (token) {
    1459            8 :             case SyntaxKind.AsyncKeyword:
    1460            8 :                 // 'async' modifier is ES2017 (async functions) or ES2018 (async generators)
    1461            8 :                 transformFlags = TransformFlags.ContainsES2017 |
    1462            8 :                     TransformFlags.ContainsES2018;
    1463            8 :                 break;
    1464            8 : 
    1465            8 :             case SyntaxKind.UsingKeyword:
    1466            8 :                 transformFlags = TransformFlags.ContainsESNext;
    1467            8 :                 break;
    1468            8 : 
    1469            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PublicKeyword:
    1470            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PrivateKeyword:
    1471            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ProtectedKeyword:
    1472            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ReadonlyKeyword:
    1473            8 :             case SyntaxKind.AbstractKeyword:
    1474            8 :             case SyntaxKind.DeclareKeyword:
    1475            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ConstKeyword:
    1476            8 :             case SyntaxKind.AnyKeyword:
    1477            8 :             case SyntaxKind.NumberKeyword:
    1478            8 :             case SyntaxKind.BigIntKeyword:
    1479            8 :             case SyntaxKind.NeverKeyword:
    1480            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ObjectKeyword:
    1481            8 :             case SyntaxKind.InKeyword:
    1482            8 :             case SyntaxKind.OutKeyword:
    1483            8 :             case SyntaxKind.OverrideKeyword:
    1484            8 :             case SyntaxKind.StringKeyword:
    1485            8 :             case SyntaxKind.BooleanKeyword:
    1486            8 :             case SyntaxKind.SymbolKeyword:
    1487            8 :             case SyntaxKind.VoidKeyword:
    1488            8 :             case SyntaxKind.UnknownKeyword:
    1489            8 :             case SyntaxKind.UndefinedKeyword: // `undefined` is an Identifier in the expression case.
    1490            8 :                 transformFlags = TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript;
    1491            8 :                 break;
    1492            8 :             case SyntaxKind.SuperKeyword:
    1493            8 :                 transformFlags = TransformFlags.ContainsES2015 | TransformFlags.ContainsLexicalSuper;
    1494            8 :                 (node as Mutable<Token<SyntaxKind.SuperKeyword>> as Mutable<SuperExpression>).flowNode = undefined; // initialized by binder (FlowContainer)
    1495            8 :                 break;
    1496            8 :             case SyntaxKind.StaticKeyword:
    1497            8 :                 transformFlags = TransformFlags.ContainsES2015;
    1498            8 :                 break;
    1499            8 :             case SyntaxKind.AccessorKeyword:
    1500            8 :                 transformFlags = TransformFlags.ContainsClassFields;
    1501            8 :                 break;
    1502            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ThisKeyword:
    1503            8 :                 // 'this' indicates a lexical 'this'
    1504            8 :                 transformFlags = TransformFlags.ContainsLexicalThis;
    1505            8 :                 (node as Mutable<Token<SyntaxKind.ThisKeyword>> as Mutable<ThisExpression>).flowNode = undefined; // initialized by binder (FlowContainer)
    1506            8 :                 break;
    1507            8 :         }
    1508            8 :         if (transformFlags) {
    1509            8 :             node.transformFlags |= transformFlags;
    1510            8 :         }
    1511            8 :         return node;
    1512            8 :     }

    1552            8 :     // @api
    1553            8 :     function createModifiersFromModifierFlags(flags: ModifierFlags) {
    1554            8 :         const result: Modifier[] = [];
    1555            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Export) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.ExportKeyword));
    1556            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Ambient) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.DeclareKeyword));
    1557            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Default) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.DefaultKeyword));
    1558            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Const) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.ConstKeyword));
    1559            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Public) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.PublicKeyword));
    1560            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Private) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.PrivateKeyword));
    1561            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Protected) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.ProtectedKeyword));
    1562            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Abstract) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.AbstractKeyword));
    1563            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Static) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.StaticKeyword));
    1564            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Override) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.OverrideKeyword));
    1565            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Readonly) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.ReadonlyKeyword));
    1566            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Accessor) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.AccessorKeyword));
    1567            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Async) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.AsyncKeyword));
    1568            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.In) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.InKeyword));
    1569            8 :         if (flags & ModifierFlags.Out) result.push(createModifier(SyntaxKind.OutKeyword));
    1570            8 :         return result.length ? result : undefined;
    1571            8 :     }

    1643            8 :     function createParameterDeclaration(
    1644            8 :         modifiers: readonly ModifierLike[] | undefined,
    1645            8 :         dotDotDotToken: DotDotDotToken | undefined,
    1646            8 :         name: string | BindingName,
    1647            8 :         questionToken?: QuestionToken,
    1648            8 :         type?: TypeNode,
    1649            8 :         initializer?: Expression,
    1650            8 :     ) {
    1651            8 :         const node = createBaseDeclaration<ParameterDeclaration>(SyntaxKind.Parameter);
    1652            8 :         node.modifiers = asNodeArray(modifiers);

    1655            8 :         node.questionToken = questionToken;
    1656            8 :         node.type = type;
    1657            8 :         node.initializer = asInitializer(initializer);
    1658            8 : 
    1659            8 :         if (isThisIdentifier(node.name)) {
    1660            8 :             node.transformFlags = TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript;
    1661            8 :         }
    1662            8 :         else {
    1663            8 :             node.transformFlags = propagateChildrenFlags(node.modifiers) |
    1664            8 :                 propagateChildFlags(node.dotDotDotToken) |
    1665            8 :                 propagateNameFlags(node.name) |
    1666            8 :                 propagateChildFlags(node.questionToken) |
    1667            8 :                 propagateChildFlags(node.initializer) |
    1668            8 :                 (node.questionToken ?? node.type ? TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript : TransformFlags.None) |
    1669            8 :                 (node.dotDotDotToken ?? node.initializer ? TransformFlags.ContainsES2015 : TransformFlags.None) |
    1670            8 :                 (modifiersToFlags(node.modifiers) & ModifierFlags.ParameterPropertyModifier ? TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScriptClassSyntax : TransformFlags.None);
    1671            8 :         }
    1672            8 : 
    1673            8 :         node.jsDoc = undefined; // initialized by parser (JsDocContainer)
    1674            8 :         return node;
    1675            8 :     }

    1762            8 :     // @api
    1763            8 :     function createPropertyDeclaration(
    1764            8 :         modifiers: readonly ModifierLike[] | undefined,
    1765            8 :         name: string | PropertyName,
    1766            8 :         questionOrExclamationToken: QuestionToken | ExclamationToken | undefined,
    1767            8 :         type: TypeNode | undefined,
    1768            8 :         initializer: Expression | undefined,
    1769            8 :     ) {
    1770            8 :         const node = createBaseDeclaration<PropertyDeclaration>(SyntaxKind.PropertyDeclaration);
    1771            8 :         node.modifiers = asNodeArray(modifiers);
    1772            8 :         node.name = asName(name);
    1773            8 :         node.questionToken = questionOrExclamationToken && isQuestionToken(questionOrExclamationToken) ? questionOrExclamationToken : undefined;
    1774            8 :         node.exclamationToken = questionOrExclamationToken && isExclamationToken(questionOrExclamationToken) ? questionOrExclamationToken : undefined;
    1775            8 :         node.type = type;
    1776            8 :         node.initializer = asInitializer(initializer);
    1777            8 : 
    1778            8 :         const isAmbient = node.flags & NodeFlags.Ambient || modifiersToFlags(node.modifiers) & ModifierFlags.Ambient;
    1779            8 : 
    1780            8 :         node.transformFlags = propagateChildrenFlags(node.modifiers) |
    1781            8 :             propagateNameFlags(node.name) |
    1782            8 :             propagateChildFlags(node.initializer) |
    1783            8 :             (isAmbient || node.questionToken || node.exclamationToken || node.type ? TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript : TransformFlags.None) |
    1784            8 :             (isComputedPropertyName(node.name) || modifiersToFlags(node.modifiers) & ModifierFlags.Static && node.initializer ? TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScriptClassSyntax : TransformFlags.None) |
    1785            8 :             TransformFlags.ContainsClassFields;
    1786            8 : 
    1787            8 :         node.jsDoc = undefined; // initialized by parser (JsDocContainer)
    1788            8 :         return node;
    1789            8 :     }
    1790            8 :

    1799            8 :     ) {

    1801            8 :                 || node.name !== name

    1803            8 :                 || node.exclamationToken !== (questionOrExclamationToken !== undefined && isExclamationToken(questionOrExclamationToken) ? questionOrExclamationToken : undefined)
    1804            8 :                 || node.type !== type

    1806            8 :             ? update(createPropertyDeclaration(modifiers, name, questionOrExclamationToken, type, initializer), node)

    1855            8 :     // @api
    1856            8 :     function createMethodDeclaration(
    1857            8 :         modifiers: readonly ModifierLike[] | undefined,
    1858            8 :         asteriskToken: AsteriskToken | undefined,
    1859            8 :         name: string | PropertyName,
    1860            8 :         questionToken: QuestionToken | undefined,
    1861            8 :         typeParameters: readonly TypeParameterDeclaration[] | undefined,
    1862            8 :         parameters: readonly ParameterDeclaration[],
    1863            8 :         type: TypeNode | undefined,
    1864            8 :         body: Block | undefined,
    1865            8 :     ) {
    1866            8 :         const node = createBaseDeclaration<MethodDeclaration>(SyntaxKind.MethodDeclaration);
    1867            8 :         node.modifiers = asNodeArray(modifiers);
    1868            8 :         node.asteriskToken = asteriskToken;
    1869            8 :         node.name = asName(name);
    1870            8 :         node.questionToken = questionToken;
    1871            8 :         node.exclamationToken = undefined; // initialized by parser for grammar errors
    1872            8 :         node.typeParameters = asNodeArray(typeParameters);
    1873            8 :         node.parameters = createNodeArray(parameters);
    1874            8 :         node.type = type;
    1875            8 :         node.body = body;
    1876            8 : 
    1877            8 :         if (!node.body) {
    1878            8 :             node.transformFlags = TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript;
    1879            8 :         }
    1880            8 :         else {
    1881            8 :             const isAsync = modifiersToFlags(node.modifiers) & ModifierFlags.Async;
    1882            8 :             const isGenerator = !!node.asteriskToken;
    1883            8 :             const isAsyncGenerator = isAsync && isGenerator;
    1884            8 : 
    1885            8 :             node.transformFlags = propagateChildrenFlags(node.modifiers) |
    1886            8 :                 propagateChildFlags(node.asteriskToken) |
    1887            8 :                 propagateNameFlags(node.name) |
    1888            8 :                 propagateChildFlags(node.questionToken) |
    1889            8 :                 propagateChildrenFlags(node.typeParameters) |
    1890            8 :                 propagateChildrenFlags(node.parameters) |
    1891            8 :                 propagateChildFlags(node.type) |
    1892            8 :                 (propagateChildFlags(node.body) & ~TransformFlags.ContainsPossibleTopLevelAwait) |
    1893            8 :                 (isAsyncGenerator ? TransformFlags.ContainsES2018 :
    1894            8 :                     isAsync ? TransformFlags.ContainsES2017 :
    1895            8 :                     isGenerator ? TransformFlags.ContainsGenerator :
    1896            8 :                     TransformFlags.None) |
    1897            8 :                 (node.questionToken || node.typeParameters || node.type ? TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript : TransformFlags.None) |
    1898            8 :                 TransformFlags.ContainsES2015;
    1899            8 :         }
    1900            8 : 
    1901            8 :         node.typeArguments = undefined; // used in quick info
    1902            8 :         node.jsDoc = undefined; // initialized by parser (JsDocContainer)
    1903            8 :         node.locals = undefined; // initialized by binder (LocalsContainer)
    1904            8 :         node.nextContainer = undefined; // initialized by binder (LocalsContainer)
    1905            8 :         node.flowNode = undefined; // initialized by binder (FlowContainer)
    1906            8 :         node.endFlowNode = undefined;
    1907            8 :         node.returnFlowNode = undefined;
    1908            8 :         return node;
    1909            8 :     }

    2029            8 :         modifiers: readonly ModifierLike[] | undefined,

    2031            8 :         parameters: readonly ParameterDeclaration[],
    2032            8 :         type: TypeNode | undefined,

    2841            8 :     function createArrayLiteralExpression(elements?: readonly Expression[], multiLine?: boolean) {
    2842            8 :         const node = createBaseNode<ArrayLiteralExpression>(SyntaxKind.ArrayLiteralExpression);
    2843            8 :         // Ensure we add a trailing comma for something like `[NumericLiteral(1), NumericLiteral(2), OmittedExpresion]` so that
    2844            8 :         // we end up with `[1, 2, ,]` instead of `[1, 2, ]` otherwise the `OmittedExpression` will just end up being treated like
    2845            8 :         // a trailing comma.
    2846            8 :         const lastElement = elements && lastOrUndefined(elements);
    2847            8 :         const elementsArray = createNodeArray(elements, lastElement && isOmittedExpression(lastElement) ? true : undefined);
    2848            8 :         node.elements = parenthesizerRules().parenthesizeExpressionsOfCommaDelimitedList(elementsArray);
    2849            8 :         node.multiLine = multiLine;
    2850            8 :         node.transformFlags |= propagateChildrenFlags(node.elements);
    2851            8 :         return node;

    3169            8 :     // @api
    3170            8 :     function createFunctionExpression(
    3171            8 :         modifiers: readonly Modifier[] | undefined,
    3172            8 :         asteriskToken: AsteriskToken | undefined,
    3173            8 :         name: string | Identifier | undefined,
    3174            8 :         typeParameters: readonly TypeParameterDeclaration[] | undefined,
    3175            8 :         parameters: readonly ParameterDeclaration[] | undefined,
    3176            8 :         type: TypeNode | undefined,
    3177            8 :         body: Block,
    3178            8 :     ) {
    3179            8 :         const node = createBaseDeclaration<FunctionExpression>(SyntaxKind.FunctionExpression);
    3180            8 :         node.modifiers = asNodeArray(modifiers);
    3181            8 :         node.asteriskToken = asteriskToken;
    3182            8 :         node.name = asName(name);
    3183            8 :         node.typeParameters = asNodeArray(typeParameters);
    3184            8 :         node.parameters = createNodeArray(parameters);
    3185            8 :         node.type = type;
    3186            8 :         node.body = body;
    3187            8 : 
    3188            8 :         const isAsync = modifiersToFlags(node.modifiers) & ModifierFlags.Async;
    3189            8 :         const isGenerator = !!node.asteriskToken;
    3190            8 :         const isAsyncGenerator = isAsync && isGenerator;
    3191            8 : 
    3192            8 :         node.transformFlags = propagateChildrenFlags(node.modifiers) |
    3193            8 :             propagateChildFlags(node.asteriskToken) |
    3194            8 :             propagateNameFlags(node.name) |
    3195            8 :             propagateChildrenFlags(node.typeParameters) |
    3196            8 :             propagateChildrenFlags(node.parameters) |
    3197            8 :             propagateChildFlags(node.type) |
    3198            8 :             (propagateChildFlags(node.body) & ~TransformFlags.ContainsPossibleTopLevelAwait) |
    3199            8 :             (isAsyncGenerator ? TransformFlags.ContainsES2018 :
    3200            8 :                 isAsync ? TransformFlags.ContainsES2017 :
    3201            8 :                 isGenerator ? TransformFlags.ContainsGenerator :
    3202            8 :                 TransformFlags.None) |
    3203            8 :             (node.typeParameters || node.type ? TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript : TransformFlags.None) |
    3204            8 :             TransformFlags.ContainsHoistedDeclarationOrCompletion;
    3205            8 : 
    3206            8 :         node.typeArguments = undefined; // used in quick info
    3207            8 :         node.jsDoc = undefined; // initialized by parser (JsDocContainer)
    3208            8 :         node.locals = undefined; // initialized by binder (LocalsContainer)
    3209            8 :         node.nextContainer = undefined; // initialized by binder (LocalsContainer)
    3210            8 :         node.flowNode = undefined; // initialized by binder (FlowContainer)
    3211            8 :         node.endFlowNode = undefined;
    3212            8 :         node.returnFlowNode = undefined;
    3213            8 :         return node;
    3214            8 :     }
    3215            8 : 
    3216            8 :     // @api
    3217            8 :     function updateFunctionExpression(
    3218            8 :         node: FunctionExpression,
    3219            8 :         modifiers: readonly Modifier[] | undefined,
    3220            8 :         asteriskToken: AsteriskToken | undefined,
    3221            8 :         name: Identifier | undefined,
    3222            8 :         typeParameters: readonly TypeParameterDeclaration[] | undefined,
    3223            8 :         parameters: readonly ParameterDeclaration[],
    3224            8 :         type: TypeNode | undefined,
    3225            8 :         body: Block,
    3226            8 :     ) {
    3227            8 :         return node.name !== name
    3228            8 :                 || node.modifiers !== modifiers
    3229            8 :                 || node.asteriskToken !== asteriskToken
    3230            8 :                 || node.typeParameters !== typeParameters
    3231            8 :                 || node.parameters !== parameters
    3232            8 :                 || node.type !== type
    3233            8 :                 || node.body !== body
    3234            8 :             ? finishUpdateBaseSignatureDeclaration(createFunctionExpression(modifiers, asteriskToken, name, typeParameters, parameters, type, body), node)
    3235            8 :             : node;
    3236            8 :     }

    3396            8 :             !isGeneratedIdentifier(node.operand) &&
    3397            8 :             !isLocalName(node.operand)
    3398            8 :         ) {
    3399            8 :             node.transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsUpdateExpressionForIdentifier;
    3400            8 :         }
    3401            8 :         return node;
    3402            8 :     }
    3403            8 : 
    3404            8 :     // @api
    3405            8 :     function updatePostfixUnaryExpression(node: PostfixUnaryExpression, operand: Expression) {
    3406            8 :         return node.operand !== operand
    3407            8 :             ? update(createPostfixUnaryExpression(operand, node.operator), node)
    3408            8 :             : node;
    3409            8 :     }
    3410            8 : 
    3411            8 :     // @api
    3412            8 :     function createBinaryExpression(left: Expression, operator: BinaryOperator | BinaryOperatorToken, right: Expression) {
    3413            8 :         const node = createBaseDeclaration<BinaryExpression>(SyntaxKind.BinaryExpression);
    3414            8 :         const operatorToken = asToken(operator);
    3415            8 :         const operatorKind = operatorToken.kind;
    3416            8 :         node.left = parenthesizerRules().parenthesizeLeftSideOfBinary(operatorKind, left);
    3417            8 :         node.operatorToken = operatorToken;
    3418            8 :         node.right = parenthesizerRules().parenthesizeRightSideOfBinary(operatorKind, node.left, right);
    3419            8 :         node.transformFlags |= propagateChildFlags(node.left) |
    3420            8 :             propagateChildFlags(node.operatorToken) |
    3421            8 :             propagateChildFlags(node.right);
    3422            8 :         if (operatorKind === SyntaxKind.QuestionQuestionToken) {
    3423            8 :             node.transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsES2020;
    3424            8 :         }
    3425            8 :         else if (operatorKind === SyntaxKind.EqualsToken) {
    3426            8 :             if (isObjectLiteralExpression(node.left)) {
    3427            8 :                 node.transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsES2015 |
    3428            8 :                     TransformFlags.ContainsES2018 |
    3429            8 :                     TransformFlags.ContainsDestructuringAssignment |
    3430            8 :                     propagateAssignmentPatternFlags(node.left);
    3431            8 :             }
    3432            8 :             else if (isArrayLiteralExpression(node.left)) {
    3433            8 :                 node.transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsES2015 |
    3434            8 :                     TransformFlags.ContainsDestructuringAssignment |
    3435            8 :                     propagateAssignmentPatternFlags(node.left);
    3436            8 :             }
    3437            8 :         }
    3438            8 :         else if (operatorKind === SyntaxKind.AsteriskAsteriskToken || operatorKind === SyntaxKind.AsteriskAsteriskEqualsToken) {
    3439            8 :             node.transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsES2016;
    3440            8 :         }
    3441            8 :         else if (isLogicalOrCoalescingAssignmentOperator(operatorKind)) {
    3442            8 :             node.transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsES2021;
    3443            8 :         }
    3444            8 :         if (operatorKind === SyntaxKind.InKeyword && isPrivateIdentifier(node.left)) {
    3445            8 :             node.transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsPrivateIdentifierInExpression;
    3446            8 :         }
    3447            8 : 
    3448            8 :         node.jsDoc = undefined; // initialized by parser (JsDocContainer)
    3449            8 :         return node;
    3450            8 :     }
    3451            8 : 
    3452            8 :     function propagateAssignmentPatternFlags(node: AssignmentPattern): TransformFlags {
    3453            8 :         return containsObjectRestOrSpread(node) ? TransformFlags.ContainsObjectRestOrSpread : TransformFlags.None;
    3454            8 :     }
    3455            8 : 
    3456            8 :     // @api
    3457            8 :     function updateBinaryExpression(node: BinaryExpression, left: Expression, operator: BinaryOperatorToken, right: Expression) {
    3458            8 :         return node.left !== left
    3459            8 :                 || node.operatorToken !== operator
    3460            8 :                 || node.right !== right
    3461            8 :             ? update(createBinaryExpression(left, operator, right), node)
    3462            8 :             : node;
    3463            8 :     }

    3466            8 :     function createConditionalExpression(condition: Expression, questionToken: QuestionToken | undefined, whenTrue: Expression, colonToken: ColonToken | undefined, whenFalse: Expression) {
    3467            8 :         const node = createBaseNode<ConditionalExpression>(SyntaxKind.ConditionalExpression);
    3468            8 :         node.condition = parenthesizerRules().parenthesizeConditionOfConditionalExpression(condition);
    3469            8 :         node.questionToken = questionToken ?? createToken(SyntaxKind.QuestionToken);
    3470            8 :         node.whenTrue = parenthesizerRules().parenthesizeBranchOfConditionalExpression(whenTrue);
    3471            8 :         node.colonToken = colonToken ?? createToken(SyntaxKind.ColonToken);
    3472            8 :         node.whenFalse = parenthesizerRules().parenthesizeBranchOfConditionalExpression(whenFalse);
    3473            8 :         node.transformFlags |= propagateChildFlags(node.condition) |
    3474            8 :             propagateChildFlags(node.questionToken) |
    3475            8 :             propagateChildFlags(node.whenTrue) |
    3476            8 :             propagateChildFlags(node.colonToken) |
    3477            8 :             propagateChildFlags(node.whenFalse);
    3478            8 :         return node;
    3479            8 :     }

    3518            8 :     function checkTemplateLiteralLikeNode(kind: TemplateLiteralToken["kind"], text: string | undefined, rawText: string | undefined, templateFlags = TokenFlags.None) {
    3519            8 :         Debug.assert(!(templateFlags & ~TokenFlags.TemplateLiteralLikeFlags), "Unsupported template flags.");
    3520            8 :         // NOTE: without the assignment to `undefined`, we don't narrow the initial type of `cooked`.
    3521            8 :         // eslint-disable-next-line no-undef-init
    3522            8 :         let cooked: string | object | undefined = undefined;
    3523            8 :         if (rawText !== undefined && rawText !== text) {
    3524            8 :             cooked = getCookedText(kind, rawText);
    3525            8 :             if (typeof cooked === "object") {
    3526            8 :                 return Debug.fail("Invalid raw text");
    3527            8 :             }
    3528            8 :         }
    3529            8 :         if (text === undefined) {
    3530            8 :             if (cooked === undefined) {
    3531            8 :                 return Debug.fail("Arguments 'text' and 'rawText' may not both be undefined.");
    3532            8 :             }
    3533            8 :             text = cooked;
    3534            8 :         }
    3535            8 :         else if (cooked !== undefined) {
    3536            8 :             Debug.assert(text === cooked, "Expected argument 'text' to be the normalized (i.e. 'cooked') version of argument 'rawText'.");
    3537            8 :         }
    3538            8 :         return text;
    3539            8 :     }
    3540            8 : 
    3541            8 :     function getTransformFlagsOfTemplateLiteralLike(templateFlags: TokenFlags) {
    3542            8 :         let transformFlags = TransformFlags.ContainsES2015;
    3543            8 :         if (templateFlags) {
    3544            8 :             transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsES2018;
    3545            8 :         }
    3546            8 :         return transformFlags;
    3547            8 :     }

    3642            8 :     function createClassExpression(
    3643            8 :         modifiers: readonly ModifierLike[] | undefined,
    3644            8 :         name: string | Identifier | undefined,
    3645            8 :         typeParameters: readonly TypeParameterDeclaration[] | undefined,
    3646            8 :         heritageClauses: readonly HeritageClause[] | undefined,

    4290            8 :     // @api
    4291            8 :     function createFunctionDeclaration(
    4292            8 :         modifiers: readonly Modifier[] | undefined,
    4293            8 :         asteriskToken: AsteriskToken | undefined,
    4294            8 :         name: string | Identifier | undefined,
    4295            8 :         typeParameters: readonly TypeParameterDeclaration[] | undefined,
    4296            8 :         parameters: readonly ParameterDeclaration[],
    4297            8 :         type: TypeNode | undefined,
    4298            8 :         body: Block | undefined,
    4299            8 :     ) {
    4300            8 :         const node = createBaseDeclaration<FunctionDeclaration>(SyntaxKind.FunctionDeclaration);
    4301            8 :         node.modifiers = asNodeArray(modifiers);
    4302            8 :         node.asteriskToken = asteriskToken;
    4303            8 :         node.name = asName(name);
    4304            8 :         node.typeParameters = asNodeArray(typeParameters);
    4305            8 :         node.parameters = createNodeArray(parameters);
    4306            8 :         node.type = type;
    4307            8 :         node.body = body;
    4308            8 : 
    4309            8 :         if (!node.body || modifiersToFlags(node.modifiers) & ModifierFlags.Ambient) {
    4310            8 :             node.transformFlags = TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript;
    4311            8 :         }
    4312            8 :         else {
    4313            8 :             const isAsync = modifiersToFlags(node.modifiers) & ModifierFlags.Async;
    4314            8 :             const isGenerator = !!node.asteriskToken;
    4315            8 :             const isAsyncGenerator = isAsync && isGenerator;
    4316            8 : 
    4317            8 :             node.transformFlags = propagateChildrenFlags(node.modifiers) |
    4318            8 :                 propagateChildFlags(node.asteriskToken) |
    4319            8 :                 propagateNameFlags(node.name) |
    4320            8 :                 propagateChildrenFlags(node.typeParameters) |
    4321            8 :                 propagateChildrenFlags(node.parameters) |
    4322            8 :                 propagateChildFlags(node.type) |
    4323            8 :                 (propagateChildFlags(node.body) & ~TransformFlags.ContainsPossibleTopLevelAwait) |
    4324            8 :                 (isAsyncGenerator ? TransformFlags.ContainsES2018 :
    4325            8 :                     isAsync ? TransformFlags.ContainsES2017 :
    4326            8 :                     isGenerator ? TransformFlags.ContainsGenerator :
    4327            8 :                     TransformFlags.None) |
    4328            8 :                 (node.typeParameters || node.type ? TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript : TransformFlags.None) |
    4329            8 :                 TransformFlags.ContainsHoistedDeclarationOrCompletion;
    4330            8 :         }
    4331            8 : 
    4332            8 :         node.typeArguments = undefined; // used in quick info
    4333            8 :         node.jsDoc = undefined; // initialized by parser (JsDocContainer)
    4334            8 :         node.locals = undefined; // initialized by binder (LocalsContainer)
    4335            8 :         node.nextContainer = undefined; // initialized by binder (LocalsContainer)
    4336            8 :         node.endFlowNode = undefined;
    4337            8 :         node.returnFlowNode = undefined;
    4338            8 :         return node;
    4339            8 :     }
    4340            8 : 
    4341            8 :     // @api
    4342            8 :     function updateFunctionDeclaration(
    4343            8 :         node: FunctionDeclaration,
    4344            8 :         modifiers: readonly Modifier[] | undefined,
    4345            8 :         asteriskToken: AsteriskToken | undefined,
    4346            8 :         name: Identifier | undefined,
    4347            8 :         typeParameters: readonly TypeParameterDeclaration[] | undefined,
    4348            8 :         parameters: readonly ParameterDeclaration[],
    4349            8 :         type: TypeNode | undefined,
    4350            8 :         body: Block | undefined,
    4351            8 :     ) {
    4352            8 :         return node.modifiers !== modifiers
    4353            8 :                 || node.asteriskToken !== asteriskToken
    4354            8 :                 || node.name !== name
    4355            8 :                 || node.typeParameters !== typeParameters
    4356            8 :                 || node.parameters !== parameters
    4357            8 :                 || node.type !== type
    4358            8 :                 || node.body !== body
    4359            8 :             ? finishUpdateFunctionDeclaration(createFunctionDeclaration(modifiers, asteriskToken, name, typeParameters, parameters, type, body), node)
    4360            8 :             : node;
    4361            8 :     }
    4362            8 : 
    4363            8 :     function finishUpdateFunctionDeclaration(updated: Mutable<FunctionDeclaration>, original: FunctionDeclaration) {
    4364            8 :         if (updated !== original) {
    4365            8 :             // copy children used only for error reporting
    4366            8 :             if (updated.modifiers === original.modifiers) {
    4367            8 :                 updated.modifiers = original.modifiers;
    4368            8 :             }
    4369            8 :         }
    4370            8 :         return finishUpdateBaseSignatureDeclaration(updated, original);
    4371            8 :     }

    4373            8 :     // @api
    4374            8 :     function createClassDeclaration(
    4375            8 :         modifiers: readonly ModifierLike[] | undefined,
    4376            8 :         name: string | Identifier | undefined,
    4377            8 :         typeParameters: readonly TypeParameterDeclaration[] | undefined,
    4378            8 :         heritageClauses: readonly HeritageClause[] | undefined,
    4379            8 :         members: readonly ClassElement[],
    4380            8 :     ) {
    4381            8 :         const node = createBaseDeclaration<ClassDeclaration>(SyntaxKind.ClassDeclaration);
    4382            8 :         node.modifiers = asNodeArray(modifiers);
    4383            8 :         node.name = asName(name);
    4384            8 :         node.typeParameters = asNodeArray(typeParameters);
    4385            8 :         node.heritageClauses = asNodeArray(heritageClauses);
    4386            8 :         node.members = createNodeArray(members);
    4387            8 : 
    4388            8 :         if (modifiersToFlags(node.modifiers) & ModifierFlags.Ambient) {
    4389            8 :             node.transformFlags = TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript;
    4390            8 :         }
    4391            8 :         else {
    4392            8 :             node.transformFlags |= propagateChildrenFlags(node.modifiers) |
    4393            8 :                 propagateNameFlags(node.name) |
    4394            8 :                 propagateChildrenFlags(node.typeParameters) |
    4395            8 :                 propagateChildrenFlags(node.heritageClauses) |
    4396            8 :                 propagateChildrenFlags(node.members) |
    4397            8 :                 (node.typeParameters ? TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript : TransformFlags.None) |
    4398            8 :                 TransformFlags.ContainsES2015;
    4399            8 :             if (node.transformFlags & TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScriptClassSyntax) {
    4400            8 :                 node.transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript;
    4401            8 :             }
    4402            8 :         }
    4403            8 : 
    4404            8 :         node.jsDoc = undefined; // initialized by parser (JsDocContainer)
    4405            8 :         return node;
    4406            8 :     }

    5855            8 :         const node = createBaseNode<HeritageClause>(SyntaxKind.HeritageClause);
    5856            8 :         node.token = token;

    5858            8 :         node.transformFlags |= propagateChildrenFlags(node.types);
    5859            8 :         switch (token) {
    5860            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ExtendsKeyword:
    5861            8 :                 node.transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsES2015;
    5862            8 :                 break;
    5863            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ImplementsKeyword:
    5864            8 :                 node.transformFlags |= TransformFlags.ContainsTypeScript;
    5865            8 :                 break;
    5866            8 :             default:
    5867            8 :                 return Debug.assertNever(token);
    5868            8 :         }
    5869            8 :         return node;
    5870            8 :     }

    6079            8 :     function createRedirectedSourceFile(redirectInfo: RedirectInfo) {
    6080            8 :         const node: SourceFile = Object.create(redirectInfo.redirectTarget);
    6081            8 :         Object.defineProperties(node, {
    6082            8 :             id: {
    6083            8 :                 get(this: SourceFile) {
    6084            8 :                     return this.redirectInfo!.redirectTarget.id;
    6085            8 :                 },
    6086            8 :                 set(this: SourceFile, value: SourceFile["id"]) {
    6087            8 :                     this.redirectInfo!.redirectTarget.id = value;
    6088            8 :                 },
    6089            8 :             },
    6090            8 :             symbol: {
    6091            8 :                 get(this: SourceFile) {
    6092            8 :                     return this.redirectInfo!.redirectTarget.symbol;
    6093            8 :                 },
    6094            8 :                 set(this: SourceFile, value: SourceFile["symbol"]) {
    6095            8 :                     this.redirectInfo!.redirectTarget.symbol = value;
    6096            8 :                 },
    6097            8 :             },
    6098            8 :         });
    6099            8 :         node.redirectInfo = redirectInfo;
    6100            8 :         return node;
    6101            8 :     }

    6103            8 :     function cloneRedirectedSourceFile(source: SourceFile) {

    6105            8 :         node.flags |= source.flags & ~NodeFlags.Synthesized;
    6106            8 :         node.fileName = source.fileName;
    6107            8 :         node.path = source.path;

    6110            8 :         node.packageJsonLocations = source.packageJsonLocations;
    6111            8 :         node.packageJsonScope = source.packageJsonScope;
    6112            8 :         node.emitNode = undefined;

    6116            8 :     function cloneSourceFileWorker(source: SourceFile) {
    6117            8 :         // TODO: This mechanism for cloning results in megamorphic property reads and writes. In future perf-related
    6118            8 :         //       work, we should consider switching explicit property assignments instead of using `for..in`.
    6119            8 :         const node = baseFactory.createBaseSourceFileNode(SyntaxKind.SourceFile) as Mutable<SourceFile>;
    6120            8 :         node.flags |= source.flags & ~NodeFlags.Synthesized;
    6121            8 :         for (const p in source) {
    6122            8 :             if (hasProperty(node, p) || !hasProperty(source, p)) {
    6123            8 :                 continue;
    6124            8 :             }
    6125            8 :             if (p === "emitNode") {
    6126            8 :                 node.emitNode = undefined;
    6127            8 :                 continue;
    6128            8 :             }
    6129            8 :             (node as any)[p] = (source as any)[p];
    6130            8 :         }
    6131            8 :         return node;
    6132            8 :     }
    6133            8 :

    6157            8 :             propagateChildFlags(node.endOfFileToken);

    6348            8 :     // @api
    6349            8 :     function cloneNode<T extends Node | undefined>(node: T): T;
    6350            8 :     function cloneNode<T extends Node>(node: T) {
    6351            8 :         // We don't use "clone" from core.ts here, as we need to preserve the prototype chain of
    6352            8 :         // the original node. We also need to exclude specific properties and only include own-
    6353            8 :         // properties (to skip members already defined on the shared prototype).
    6354            8 :         if (node === undefined) {
    6355            8 :             return node;
    6356            8 :         }
    6357            8 :         if (isSourceFile(node)) {
    6358            8 :             return cloneSourceFile(node) as T & SourceFile;
    6359            8 :         }
    6360            8 :         if (isGeneratedIdentifier(node)) {
    6361            8 :             return cloneGeneratedIdentifier(node) as T & GeneratedIdentifier;
    6362            8 :         }
    6363            8 :         if (isIdentifier(node)) {
    6364            8 :             return cloneIdentifier(node) as T & Identifier;
    6365            8 :         }
    6366            8 :         if (isGeneratedPrivateIdentifier(node)) {
    6367            8 :             return cloneGeneratedPrivateIdentifier(node) as T & GeneratedPrivateIdentifier;
    6368            8 :         }
    6369            8 :         if (isPrivateIdentifier(node)) {
    6370            8 :             return clonePrivateIdentifier(node) as T & PrivateIdentifier;
    6371            8 :         }
    6372            8 : 
    6373            8 :         const clone = !isNodeKind(node.kind) ? baseFactory.createBaseTokenNode(node.kind) as T :
    6374            8 :             baseFactory.createBaseNode(node.kind) as T;
    6375            8 : 
    6376            8 :         (clone as Mutable<T>).flags |= node.flags & ~NodeFlags.Synthesized;
    6377            8 :         (clone as Mutable<T>).transformFlags = node.transformFlags;
    6378            8 :         setOriginal(clone, node);
    6379            8 : 
    6380            8 :         for (const key in node) {
    6381            8 :             if (hasProperty(clone, key) || !hasProperty(node, key)) {
    6382            8 :                 continue;
    6383            8 :             }
    6384            8 : 
    6385            8 :             clone[key] = node[key];
    6386            8 :         }
    6387            8 : 
    6388            8 :         return clone;
    6389            8 :     }

    6534            8 :

    6536            8 :         isData = tryAddPropertyAssignment(properties, "value", attributes.value) || isData;
    6537            8 : 
    6538            8 :         let isAccessor = tryAddPropertyAssignment(properties, "get", attributes.get);
    6539            8 :         isAccessor = tryAddPropertyAssignment(properties, "set", attributes.set) || isAccessor;
    6540            8 :

    6545            8 :     function updateOuterExpression(outerExpression: OuterExpression, expression: Expression) {
    6546            8 :         switch (outerExpression.kind) {
    6547            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ParenthesizedExpression:
    6548            8 :                 return updateParenthesizedExpression(outerExpression, expression);
    6549            8 :             case SyntaxKind.TypeAssertionExpression:
    6550            8 :                 return updateTypeAssertion(outerExpression, outerExpression.type, expression);
    6551            8 :             case SyntaxKind.AsExpression:
    6552            8 :                 return updateAsExpression(outerExpression, expression, outerExpression.type);
    6553            8 :             case SyntaxKind.SatisfiesExpression:
    6554            8 :                 return updateSatisfiesExpression(outerExpression, expression, outerExpression.type);
    6555            8 :             case SyntaxKind.NonNullExpression:
    6556            8 :                 return updateNonNullExpression(outerExpression, expression);
    6557            8 :             case SyntaxKind.PartiallyEmittedExpression:
    6558            8 :                 return updatePartiallyEmittedExpression(outerExpression, expression);
    6559            8 :         }
    6560            8 :     }
    6561            8 : 
    6562            8 :     /**
    6563            8 :      * Determines whether a node is a parenthesized expression that can be ignored when recreating outer expressions.
    6564            8 :      *
    6565            8 :      * A parenthesized expression can be ignored when all of the following are true:
    6566            8 :      *
    6567            8 :      * - It's `pos` and `end` are not -1
    6568            8 :      * - It does not have a custom source map range
    6569            8 :      * - It does not have a custom comment range
    6570            8 :      * - It does not have synthetic leading or trailing comments
    6571            8 :      *
    6572            8 :      * If an outermost parenthesized expression is ignored, but the containing expression requires a parentheses around
    6573            8 :      * the expression to maintain precedence, a new parenthesized expression should be created automatically when
    6574            8 :      * the containing expression is created/updated.
    6575            8 :      */
    6576            8 :     function isIgnorableParen(node: Expression) {
    6577            8 :         return isParenthesizedExpression(node)
    6578            8 :             && nodeIsSynthesized(node)
    6579            8 :             && nodeIsSynthesized(getSourceMapRange(node))
    6580            8 :             && nodeIsSynthesized(getCommentRange(node))
    6581            8 :             && !some(getSyntheticLeadingComments(node))
    6582            8 :             && !some(getSyntheticTrailingComments(node));
    6583            8 :     }
    6584            8 : 
    6585            8 :     function restoreOuterExpressions(outerExpression: Expression | undefined, innerExpression: Expression, kinds = OuterExpressionKinds.All): Expression {
    6586            8 :         if (outerExpression && isOuterExpression(outerExpression, kinds) && !isIgnorableParen(outerExpression)) {
    6587            8 :             return updateOuterExpression(
    6588            8 :                 outerExpression,
    6589            8 :                 restoreOuterExpressions(outerExpression.expression, innerExpression),
    6590            8 :             );

    6612            8 :     function shouldBeCapturedInTempVariable(node: Expression, cacheIdentifiers: boolean): boolean {
    6613            8 :         const target = skipParentheses(node);
    6614            8 :         switch (target.kind) {
    6615            8 :             case SyntaxKind.Identifier:
    6616            8 :                 return cacheIdentifiers;
    6617            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ThisKeyword:
    6618            8 :             case SyntaxKind.NumericLiteral:
    6619            8 :             case SyntaxKind.BigIntLiteral:
    6620            8 :             case SyntaxKind.StringLiteral:
    6621            8 :                 return false;
    6622            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ArrayLiteralExpression:
    6623            8 :                 const elements = (target as ArrayLiteralExpression).elements;
    6624            8 :                 if (elements.length === 0) {
    6625            8 :                     return false;
    6626            8 :                 }
    6627            8 :                 return true;
    6628            8 :             case SyntaxKind.ObjectLiteralExpression:
    6629            8 :                 return (target as ObjectLiteralExpression).properties.length > 0;
    6630            8 :             default:
    6631            8 :                 return true;
    6632            8 :         }
    6633            8 :     }

    6635            8 :     function createCallBinding(expression: Expression, recordTempVariable: (temp: Identifier) => void, languageVersion?: ScriptTarget, cacheIdentifiers = false): CallBinding {
    6636            8 :         const callee = skipOuterExpressions(expression, OuterExpressionKinds.All);
    6637            8 :         let thisArg: Expression;
    6638            8 :         let target: LeftHandSideExpression;
    6639            8 :         if (isSuperProperty(callee)) {
    6640            8 :             thisArg = createThis();
    6641            8 :             target = callee;
    6642            8 :         }
    6643            8 :         else if (isSuperKeyword(callee)) {
    6644            8 :             thisArg = createThis();
    6645            8 :             target = languageVersion !== undefined && languageVersion < ScriptTarget.ES2015
    6646            8 :                 ? setTextRange(createIdentifier("_super"), callee)
    6647            8 :                 : callee as PrimaryExpression;
    6648            8 :         }
    6649            8 :         else if (getEmitFlags(callee) & EmitFlags.HelperName) {
    6650            8 :             thisArg = createVoidZero();
    6651            8 :             target = parenthesizerRules().parenthesizeLeftSideOfAccess(callee, /*optionalChain*/ false);
    6652            8 :         }
    6653            8 :         else if (isPropertyAccessExpression(callee)) {
    6654            8 :             if (shouldBeCapturedInTempVariable(callee.expression, cacheIdentifiers)) {
    6655            8 :                 // for `a.b()` target is `(_a = a).b` and thisArg is `_a`
    6656            8 :                 thisArg = createTempVariable(recordTempVariable);
    6657            8 :                 target = createPropertyAccessExpression(
    6658            8 :                     setTextRange(
    6659            8 :                         factory.createAssignment(
    6660            8 :                             thisArg,
    6661            8 :                             callee.expression,
    6662            8 :                         ),
    6663            8 :                         callee.expression,
    6664            8 :                     ),
    6665            8 :                     callee.name,
    6666            8 :                 );
    6667            8 :                 setTextRange(target, callee);
    6668            8 :             }
    6669            8 :             else {
    6670            8 :                 thisArg = callee.expression;
    6671            8 :                 target = callee;
    6672            8 :             }
    6673            8 :         }
    6674            8 :         else if (isElementAccessExpression(callee)) {
    6675            8 :             if (shouldBeCapturedInTempVariable(callee.expression, cacheIdentifiers)) {
    6676            8 :                 // for `a[b]()` target is `(_a = a)[b]` and thisArg is `_a`
    6677            8 :                 thisArg = createTempVariable(recordTempVariable);
    6678            8 :                 target = createElementAccessExpression(
    6679            8 :                     setTextRange(
    6680            8 :                         factory.createAssignment(
    6681            8 :                             thisArg,
    6682            8 :                             callee.expression,
    6683            8 :                         ),
    6684            8 :                         callee.expression,
    6685            8 :                     ),
    6686            8 :                     callee.argumentExpression,
    6687            8 :                 );
    6688            8 :                 setTextRange(target, callee);
    6689            8 :             }
    6690            8 :             else {
    6691            8 :                 thisArg = callee.expression;
    6692            8 :                 target = callee;
    6693            8 :             }
    6694            8 :         }
    6695            8 :         else {
    6696            8 :             // for `a()` target is `a` and thisArg is `void 0`
    6697            8 :             thisArg = createVoidZero();
    6698            8 :             target = parenthesizerRules().parenthesizeLeftSideOfAccess(expression, /*optionalChain*/ false);
    6699            8 :         }
    6700            8 : 
    6701            8 :         return { target, thisArg };
    6702            8 :     }

    6855            8 :     function isUseStrictPrologue(node: ExpressionStatement): boolean {
    6856            8 :         return isStringLiteral(node.expression) && node.expression.text === "use strict";
    6857            8 :     }
    6858            8 : 
    6859            8 :     function createUseStrictPrologue() {
    6860            8 :         return startOnNewLine(createExpressionStatement(createStringLiteral("use strict"))) as PrologueDirective;
    6861            8 :     }
    6862            8 : 
    6863            8 :     /**
    6864            8 :      * Copies only the standard (string-expression) prologue-directives into the target statement-array.
    6865            8 :      * @param source origin statements array
    6866            8 :      * @param target result statements array
    6867            8 :      * @param statementOffset The offset at which to begin the copy.
    6868            8 :      * @param ensureUseStrict boolean determining whether the function need to add prologue-directives
    6869            8 :      * @returns Count of how many directive statements were copied.
    6870            8 :      */
    6871            8 :     function copyStandardPrologue(source: readonly Statement[], target: Statement[], statementOffset = 0, ensureUseStrict?: boolean): number {
    6872            8 :         Debug.assert(target.length === 0, "Prologue directives should be at the first statement in the target statements array");
    6873            8 :         let foundUseStrict = false;
    6874            8 :         const numStatements = source.length;
    6875            8 :         while (statementOffset < numStatements) {
    6876            8 :             const statement = source[statementOffset];
    6877            8 :             if (isPrologueDirective(statement)) {
    6878            8 :                 if (isUseStrictPrologue(statement)) {
    6879            8 :                     foundUseStrict = true;
    6880            8 :                 }
    6881            8 :                 target.push(statement);
    6882            8 :             }
    6883            8 :             else {
    6884            8 :                 break;
    6885            8 :             }
    6886            8 :             statementOffset++;
    6887            8 :         }
    6888            8 :         if (ensureUseStrict && !foundUseStrict) {
    6889            8 :             target.push(createUseStrictPrologue());
    6890            8 :         }
    6891            8 :         return statementOffset;
    6892            8 :     }

    6894            8 :     /**
    6895            8 :      * Copies only the custom prologue-directives into target statement-array.
    6896            8 :      * @param source origin statements array
    6897            8 :      * @param target result statements array
    6898            8 :      * @param statementOffset The offset at which to begin the copy.
    6899            8 :      * @param visitor Optional callback used to visit any custom prologue directives.
    6900            8 :      */
    6901            8 :     function copyCustomPrologue(source: readonly Statement[], target: Statement[], statementOffset: number, visitor?: (node: Node) => VisitResult<Node>, filter?: (node: Statement) => boolean): number;
    6902            8 :     function copyCustomPrologue(source: readonly Statement[], target: Statement[], statementOffset: number | undefined, visitor?: (node: Node) => VisitResult<Node>, filter?: (node: Statement) => boolean): number | undefined;
    6903            8 :     function copyCustomPrologue(source: readonly Statement[], target: Statement[], statementOffset: number | undefined, visitor?: (node: Node) => VisitResult<Node>, filter: (node: Statement) => boolean = returnTrue): number | undefined {
    6904            8 :         const numStatements = source.length;
    6905            8 :         while (statementOffset !== undefined && statementOffset < numStatements) {
    6906            8 :             const statement = source[statementOffset];
    6907            8 :             if (getEmitFlags(statement) & EmitFlags.CustomPrologue && filter(statement)) {
    6908            8 :                 append(target, visitor ? visitNode(statement, visitor, isStatement) : statement);
    6909            8 :             }
    6910            8 :             else {
    6911            8 :                 break;
    6912            8 :             }
    6913            8 :             statementOffset++;
    6914            8 :         }
    6915            8 :         return statementOffset;
    6916            8 :     }

    6943            8 :     function findSpanEnd<T>(array: readonly T[], test: (value: T) => boolean, start: number) {
    6944            8 :         let i = start;
    6945            8 :         while (i < array.length && test(array[i])) {
    6946            8 :             i++;
    6947            8 :         }
    6948            8 :         return i;
    6949            8 :     }

    6951            8 :     function mergeLexicalEnvironment(statements: NodeArray<Statement>, declarations: readonly Statement[] | undefined): NodeArray<Statement>;
    6952            8 :     function mergeLexicalEnvironment(statements: Statement[], declarations: readonly Statement[] | undefined): Statement[];
    6953            8 :     function mergeLexicalEnvironment(statements: Statement[] | NodeArray<Statement>, declarations: readonly Statement[] | undefined) {
    6954            8 :         if (!some(declarations)) {
    6955            8 :             return statements;
    6956            8 :         }
    6957            8 : 
    6958            8 :         // When we merge new lexical statements into an existing statement list, we merge them in the following manner:
    6959            8 :         //
    6960            8 :         // Given:
    6961            8 :         //
    6962            8 :         // | Left                               | Right                               |
    6963            8 :         // |------------------------------------|-------------------------------------|
    6964            8 :         // | [standard prologues (left)]        | [standard prologues (right)]        |
    6965            8 :         // | [hoisted functions (left)]         | [hoisted functions (right)]         |
    6966            8 :         // | [hoisted variables (left)]         | [hoisted variables (right)]         |
    6967            8 :         // | [lexical init statements (left)]   | [lexical init statements (right)]   |
    6968            8 :         // | [other statements (left)]          |                                     |
    6969            8 :         //
    6970            8 :         // The resulting statement list will be:
    6971            8 :         //
    6972            8 :         // | Result                              |
    6973            8 :         // |-------------------------------------|
    6974            8 :         // | [standard prologues (right)]        |
    6975            8 :         // | [standard prologues (left)]         |
    6976            8 :         // | [hoisted functions (right)]         |
    6977            8 :         // | [hoisted functions (left)]          |
    6978            8 :         // | [hoisted variables (right)]         |
    6979            8 :         // | [hoisted variables (left)]          |
    6980            8 :         // | [lexical init statements (right)]   |
    6981            8 :         // | [lexical init statements (left)]    |
    6982            8 :         // | [other statements (left)]           |
    6983            8 :         //
    6984            8 :         // NOTE: It is expected that new lexical init statements must be evaluated before existing lexical init statements,
    6985            8 :         // as the prior transformation may depend on the evaluation of the lexical init statements to be in the correct state.
    6986            8 : 
    6987            8 :         // find standard prologues on left in the following order: standard directives, hoisted functions, hoisted variables, other custom
    6988            8 :         const leftStandardPrologueEnd = findSpanEnd(statements, isPrologueDirective, 0);
    6989            8 :         const leftHoistedFunctionsEnd = findSpanEnd(statements, isHoistedFunction, leftStandardPrologueEnd);
    6990            8 :         const leftHoistedVariablesEnd = findSpanEnd(statements, isHoistedVariableStatement, leftHoistedFunctionsEnd);
    6991            8 : 
    6992            8 :         // find standard prologues on right in the following order: standard directives, hoisted functions, hoisted variables, other custom
    6993            8 :         const rightStandardPrologueEnd = findSpanEnd(declarations, isPrologueDirective, 0);
    6994            8 :         const rightHoistedFunctionsEnd = findSpanEnd(declarations, isHoistedFunction, rightStandardPrologueEnd);
    6995            8 :         const rightHoistedVariablesEnd = findSpanEnd(declarations, isHoistedVariableStatement, rightHoistedFunctionsEnd);
    6996            8 :         const rightCustomPrologueEnd = findSpanEnd(declarations, isCustomPrologue, rightHoistedVariablesEnd);
    6997            8 :         Debug.assert(rightCustomPrologueEnd === declarations.length, "Expected declarations to be valid standard or custom prologues");
    6998            8 : 
    6999            8 :         // splice prologues from the right into the left. We do this in reverse order
    7000            8 :         // so that we don't need to recompute the index on the left when we insert items.
    7001            8 :         const left = isNodeArray(statements) ? statements.slice() : statements;
    7002            8 : 
    7003            8 :         // splice other custom prologues from right into left
    7004            8 :         if (rightCustomPrologueEnd > rightHoistedVariablesEnd) {
    7005            8 :             left.splice(leftHoistedVariablesEnd, 0, ...declarations.slice(rightHoistedVariablesEnd, rightCustomPrologueEnd));
    7006            8 :         }
    7007            8 : 
    7008            8 :         // splice hoisted variables from right into left
    7009            8 :         if (rightHoistedVariablesEnd > rightHoistedFunctionsEnd) {
    7010            8 :             left.splice(leftHoistedFunctionsEnd, 0, ...declarations.slice(rightHoistedFunctionsEnd, rightHoistedVariablesEnd));
    7011            8 :         }
    7012            8 : 
    7013            8 :         // splice hoisted functions from right into left
    7014            8 :         if (rightHoistedFunctionsEnd > rightStandardPrologueEnd) {
    7015            8 :             left.splice(leftStandardPrologueEnd, 0, ...declarations.slice(rightStandardPrologueEnd, rightHoistedFunctionsEnd));
    7016            8 :         }
    7017            8 : 
    7018            8 :         // splice standard prologues from right into left (that are not already in left)
    7019            8 :         if (rightStandardPrologueEnd > 0) {
    7020            8 :             if (leftStandardPrologueEnd === 0) {
    7021            8 :                 left.splice(0, 0, ...declarations.slice(0, rightStandardPrologueEnd));
    7022            8 :             }
    7023            8 :             else {
    7024            8 :                 const leftPrologues = new Map<string, boolean>();
